Each layer communicates via event packets composed of symbolic and numerical data. Only the modules relevant to a given context activate—mirroring spiking neural dynamics for maximal energy efficiency.

\subsection{Subsystem Functions}
\begin{itemize}[leftmargin=1.5em]
  \item \textbf{Perception \& Action Interface:} Transforms sensory and API inputs into unified semantic events.
  \item \textbf{Cognitive Substrate:} Mesh of micro-minds responsible for reasoning, abstraction, and creativity.
  \item \textbf{Memory Fabric:} Comprises episodic, semantic, and procedural memories with vectorized representations.
  \item \textbf{Self-Model Layer:} Maintains awareness of system state, performance, and resource utilization.
  \item \textbf{Evolution Engine:} Conducts structural mutations, selection, and merging of improved reasoning modules.
  \item \textbf{Energy \& Ethos Core:} Regulates energy efficiency and enforces ethical decision boundaries.
  \item \textbf{Distributed Systems Layer:} Enables multi-agent operation across cloud, edge, and robotic environments.
\end{itemize}

