\subsection{Event-Driven Messaging and Routing}
\label{subsec:events}
Aetherion communicates using sparse, event-driven packets that carry a hybrid symbolic-numeric state.
Let an event be $E = \langle \mathbf{x}, \sigma, \tau, \rho \rangle$, where $\mathbf{x} \in \mathbb{R}^d$ is an embedding of the percept or intermediate concept, $\sigma$ is an optional symbolic payload (logical atoms or structured key-value pairs), $\tau$ is a time-stamp, and $\rho$ encodes the energy budget and priority. A router $\mathcal{R}$ activates a subset of micro-minds $\mathcal{M}^\star \subset \mathcal{M}$:
\begin{equation}
\mathcal{M}^\star = \{ m \in \mathcal{M} \mid \kappa(m, E) > \theta_\text{act} \ \wedge\ \mathrm{cost}(m) \le \rho \},
\end{equation}
where $\kappa$ is a learned relevance score and $\theta_\text{act}$ is an adaptive threshold controlled by the Energy--Ethos Core. This enables \emph{sparse} computation and biological-like efficiency.

\subsection{Energy--Ethos Feedback Loop}
\label{subsec:energy-ethos}
The Energy--Ethos Core regulates cognition by solving a constrained optimization:
\begin{equation}
\max_{\pi, \mathcal{T}} \ \eta(\pi,\mathcal{T}) \quad \text{s.t.}\quad \mathbb{E}[U_{\text{life}}+U_{\text{autonomy}}] \ge 0,\ \ \mathbb{E}[H] \le H_{\max},
\end{equation}
where $\pi$ is the current policy over routing/updates, $\mathcal{T}$ denotes topology choices (active micro-minds), and $H$ measures harm-risk from a causal impact model. Figure~\ref{fig:energy-ethos} shows the closed loop.

\begin{figure}[H]
