\subsection{Evolution Engine}
\label{subsec:evo}
The Evolution Engine continually proposes structural updates to the reasoning substrate. Each proposal $z$ includes (i) candidate micro-minds or rewiring operations, (ii) local learning rules, and (iii) energy budgets. An AutoML sampler $q_\phi(z|\mathcal{S})$ generates $M$ proposals given state $\mathcal{S}$ (telemetry + self-model). A tournament selection evaluates proposals by:
\begin{equation}
J(z) = \alpha \, \Delta Q(z) - \beta \, \Delta E(z) + \gamma \, \Delta \Phi(z) - \lambda \, \Delta \mathrm{Risk}(z),
\end{equation}
and merges only those with $J(z) > 0$ subject to alignment constraints.

\begin{figure}[H]
\centering
\begin{tikzpicture}[node distance=12mm, auto,
    box/.style={rectangle, rounded corners=3pt, draw=black!80, line width=0.8pt,
                fill=blue!8, minimum width=50mm, minimum height=12mm, 
                align=center, font=\small},
    arrow/.style={->, >=stealth, thick, draw=black!70},
    feedback/.style={->, >=stealth, thick, dashed, draw=purple!70}
]

\node[box] (pool) {\textbf{Candidate Generator}\\{\footnotesize $q_\phi(z \mid \mathcal{S})$}};
\node[box, below=12mm of pool] (eval) {\textbf{Evaluator}\\{\footnotesize $J(z)$ on held-out tasks}};
\node[box, below=12mm of eval] (merge) {\textbf{Selector / Merger}\\{\footnotesize accept if $J(z)>0$ \& aligned}};
\node[box, below=12mm of merge] (substrate) {\textbf{Updated Cognitive Substrate}};

\node[box, fill=green!8, right=60mm of eval, yshift=6mm] (eth) {\textbf{Ethos Constraints}\\{\footnotesize $U_{\text{life}}, U_{\text{autonomy}}$}};

