\appendix
\section{Appendix A: Derivation of Free-Energy Gradients}
Let the expected free energy $G$ factorize as
\[
G = \mathbb{E}_{q(s',a')}[R(s',a') + \mathrm{KL}(q(s'|a')||p(s'))],
\]
where $R$ denotes reward or evidence term.  
Taking the derivative with respect to policy parameters $\theta$:
\[
\nabla_\theta G = \mathbb{E}_{q(s',a')}\!\left[ \nabla_\theta \log q(a'|\theta) \, (R(s',a') - \log q(s'|a') + \log p(s')) \right].
\]
This gradient is used for updating routing policies in the Evolution Engine.

\section{Appendix B: Pseudocode for Energy Scheduler}
\begin{algorithm}[H]
\caption{Energy Budget Scheduler}
\begin{algorithmic}[1]
\Require Active modules $\mathcal{M}^\star$, telemetry $\mathcal{S}$
\State Compute current power draw $E_\text{curr}$ and predicted demand $E_\text{pred}$
\If{$E_\text{curr} > E_\text{budget}$}
  \State Reduce thresholds $\theta_\text{act} \gets \theta_\text{act} + \delta$
  \State Suspend least informative modules
\Else
  \State Gradually restore suspended modules
\EndIf
\State Log energy metrics for Ethos Core audit
\end{algorithmic}
\end{algorithm}

\section{Appendix C: Event Schema Specification}
Each event packet is stored as:
\begin{verbatim}
{
  "id": UUID,
  "embedding": [float],
  "symbolic": "concept-token",
  "timestamp": float,
  "energy_budget": float,
  "priority": float,
  "trace_id": UUID
}
\end{verbatim}

\section{Appendix D: Reproducible Figure Sources}
\label{app:tikz-sources}
To enable community replication and modification, we provide TikZ source code for all major architectural diagrams. Complete \LaTeX~source is available at:

\texttt{https://github.com/nelieo-research/aetherion-paper}

\paragraph{Key Packages Required:}
\begin{verbatim}
\usepackage{tikz}
\usetikzlibrary{positioning,arrows.meta,calc,shapes.geometric}
\usepackage{pgfplots}
\pgfplotsset{compat=1.18}
\end{verbatim}

\paragraph{Figure Compilation:}
All TikZ figures compile with \texttt{pdflatex} without external dependencies. For standalone figure generation:
\begin{verbatim}
pdflatex -jobname=fig_arch aetherion_paper.tex
\end{verbatim}

\paragraph{Customization Guidelines:}
\begin{itemize}[leftmargin=1.5em]
  \item Node colors defined as \texttt{fill=blue!15} can be adjusted for accessibility.
  \item Font sizes use \texttt{\textbackslash footnotesize} for labels; scale as needed.
  \item Coordinate positions use millimeter units for precision.
  \item All figures designed for grayscale-friendly printing.
\end{itemize}

